iIn Norse mythology, Heimdallr is a god who possesses the resounding
ihorn Gjallarhorn, owns the golden-maned horse Gulltoppr, is called the
ishining god and the whitest of the gods, has gold teeth, and is the son
iof Nine Mothers (who may represent personified waves). Heimdallr is
iattested as possessing foreknowledge, keen eyesight and hearing, and
ikeeps watch for invaders and the onset of Ragnarök while drinking fine
imead in his dwelling Himinbjörg, located where the burning rainbow bridge
iBifröst meets the sky. Heimdallr is said to be the originator of social
iclasses among humanity and once regained Freyja's treasured possession
iBrísingamen while doing battle in the shape of a seal with Loki.
iHeimdallr and Loki are foretold to kill one another during the events
iof Ragnarök. Heimdallr is additionally referred to as Rig, Hallinskiði,
iGullintanni, and Vindlér or Vindhlér.
